caption.text:
Just a quick post
.
I picked this amazing game over the weekend
.
Hollow Knight
.
I had bought it digitally at first but having liked what I played so much I just had to get a physical copy
.
#hollowknight #hollowknightsilksong #teamcherry #teamcherrygames #fangamer #nintendo #switch #nintendoswitch #metroidvania #rpg #videogames #games #gaming #gamer #retrogaming #retrogames #gamersunite

Been playing some Archlion Saga with my new Hori d-pad joycon. So far it feels nice. I haven't had to use the buttons on it much but the shoulder buttons feel a little nicer and the minus button is taller and more rubbery so it's easier to hit. The d=pad is nice but there's not the most space for holding it while using the pad so it's a bit of an adjustment. Still feels better than using the buttons or stick to move in a 2D game like this. I notice it's a tiny bit lighter than the regular joycons but it doesn't require any charging since it just has to stay connected anyway so that's nice.
.
The game itself is pretty interesting so far, especially for a cheap game that was advertised as an adequate, easily completable adventure. It's a simple RPG that doesn't want you to get lost or sink tons of hours into it, and as someone who likes simpler RPGs I can appreciate the convenience of it while still finding the style nice enough. .

-
El objetivo de este set es usar las resistencias y la presión que mete Bisharp para lograr un cambio seguro y aumentar su Ataque, aprovechando los momentos en los que el rival use defog para recibir un +2 de Ataque gratis.
-
Danza espada para aumentar el Ataque.
-
Desarme para quitar objetos y como ataque de STAB más fiable, golpe Bajo como ataque de prioridad.
-
Cabeza de Hierro por cobertura frente a Pokémon de tipo Hada y como STAB secundario.
-
Patada baja se puede usar sobre Danza Espada si necesitas cobertura extra frente al tipo Acero (notablemente frente a otro Bisharp).

On the switch lite posts and previous joycon posts there are an alarming amount of people trying to say it's our faults that the controllers drift. caption.text:
Happy birthday to me!
.
My birthday was a few days ago now, but I completely forgot to post these! Oh man, my ‘to-play’ list has reached insane territory. I’m not sure I can get through all these games in a single lifetime. 😅
.
Dragon Quest XI S: Echoes of an Elusive Age - Definitive Edition — I started playing DQXI on PS4 when it was first released, and I fell in love with it. My first DQ game. While the graphics were gorgeous on the PS4 Pro, I couldn’t help but get mildly annoyed at the synthesised soundtrack and not being able to take such a long game with me on the go. So I stopped playing and waited for the Switch version. Glad I did, it’s super impressive on the Switch, and while there is absolutely a graphical difference, I think I’m OK with it for the other benefits I get.
.
Fire Emblem: Three Houses — I always intended to play this game, just not at launch. I’ve never played a Fire Emblem game before, and while strategy RPGs aren’t usually my jam, I’ve heard nothing but good things about this one. And the Persona-esque school setting to roam around in makes it hard to resist.
.
Ni No Kuni: Wrath of the White Witch - Remastered — I debated picking up the regular version for Switch, but I have the sequel on PS4 and kind of like each series of games to be on the same platform. Another RPG that looks gorgeous but also deep and whimsical at the same time. Can’t wait to dive in.
.
Man of Medan — Oh boy... Started playing this last night with my partner (there’s no way in hell I was going to play it on my own!!) and it’s sooo good. I love how the multiplayer couch co-op is called ‘Movie Night’ because that’s exactly how it felt. We haven’t finished it yet, but played a good chunk of it (with all the lights off, of course) and I can’t wait to get back to it ASAP!
.
Which one of these games is your favourite, or your most anticipated, and why?
.
.
.
.

-Switch Lite Başarısı-
Nintendo Switch oyun konsolunun daha uygun modeli olan Switch Lite, Japonya pazarında ilk 3 günde adeta yok sattı. Switch Lite, Japonya’da şu ana kadar ilk haftada en çok satış yapan ikinci oyun konsolu oldu. Nintendo’nun borsadaki hisseleri ise geçtiğimiz günlerde yüzde 4’ten fazla düşüş yaşadı, çünkü yatırımcılar Switch Lite konsolunun iyi satış yapmadığını düşünüyordu. Ancak, Famitsu Magazine’nin verilerine göre durum hiç öyle görünmüyor. Verilere göre Nintendo Switch Lite oyun konsolu, adeta yok sattı ve Japonya’da başlangıç satış rakamı olarak en çok satılan konsollardan birisi oldu.

Links Awakening 100% done 🎮
I never played the original version of this game and I refused to use a walkthrough. It took me a good 35 hours to 100% it. For those saying it's a short game I agree it is for a Zelda game. The puzzles are simple enough but finding all the shells and heart pieces was difficult.

WARRIORS OROCHI 4 ULTIMATE RILIS BULAN DESEMBER DI JEPANG

Koei Tecmo selaku publisher, bekerja sama dengan Omega Force, mengumumkan mengenai tanggal rilis Warriors Orochi 4 Ultimate. Di Jepang, game tersebut bakal tersedia di pasaran pada tanggal 19 Desember mendatang, dengan banderol harga 7.800 yen. Mereka juga memamerkan dua sosok tambahan yakni Achilles (dari Warriors: Legend of Troy), serta Hades yang merupakan karakter baru.
